This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the extraction of dependency grammars and syntax-to-semantic-relationship mappings from large text corpora. It also mentions prior work with natural language comprehension and generation systems. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it mentions prior work from the statistical language learning literature. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the development of a natural language comprehension and generation system. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper mentions the use of neural networks in prior work. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the extraction of information from unannotated text corpora.
